article.headline: Green Bay 60, Indiana St. 59
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. -- Rahmon Fletcher scored a game-high 22 points as Wisconsin-Green Bay defeated Indiana State, 60-59, in a BracketBuster game on Saturday night. The Phoenix (19-10, 10-6 Horizon) trailed 52-45 after the Sycamores' (16-12, 8-8 Missouri Valley) Rashad Reed hit a 3-pointer with just 7:58 left to play. With 3:29 left, Fletcher would hit a jumper to cut the lead to just one, 56-55. Fletcher would hit a 3 to give the Phoenix their first lead of the half at 58-56 with 1:55 left. With 38-seconds left Reed would answer back with a 3-pointer to put his team up 59-58. Fletcher's biggest bucket of the game came with just 11-seconds left as he put the Phoenix ahead 60-59. Rian Pearson had 17 points, hitting on 7 of 10 from the floor for the Phoenix. Koang Duoluony led the Sycamores with 14 points. Carl Richard had seven points and a game-high 14 rebounds.
